  "prompt": "How would you know that a guy has a crush on you or likes you even though if you are friends?",
  "response": "Figuring out whether a guy has a crush on you, especially if you're already friends, can sometimes be tricky. However, there are several signs that may indicate his feelings:\n\n1. **Increased Attention**: He\u2019s more attentive to you than to other friends. If he always seems to be available to talk or hang out and responds quickly to your messages, it could be a sign that he likes you.\n\n2. **Physical Contact**: He might find excuses to touch you, like a casual brush on the arm or a playful push.\n\n3. **Compliments**: If he frequently compliments your appearance, intelligence, or personality in a way that feels more intense or frequent than usual, he might be interested in you.\n\n4. **Eye Contact**: Prolonged eye contact or looking at you a lot when you\u2019re not paying attention could indicate his interest.\n\n5. **Body Language**: Pay attention to his body language. If he faces you during conversations, mirrors your gestures, or leans in when talking, he may be attracted to you.\n\n6. **Jealousy**: He might show signs of jealousy or discomfort when you talk about other guys or go on dates.\n\n7. **Remembering Details**: If he remembers little details about your likes, dislikes, and stories you\u2019ve told him, it shows he\u2019s paying special attention to you.\n\n8. **Teasing and Flirting**: Playful teasing or flirtatious behavior that goes beyond what he does with other friends can be a sign.\n\n9. **Making Time for You**: He goes out of his way to spend time with you, even if he has a busy schedule.\n\n10. **Asking Personal Questions**: If he starts asking you more personal questions, it could be a sign that he's trying to get to know you on a deeper level.\n\nDirect communication is often the best way to understand someone's feelings, but these signs can help you gauge his interest.",
